From: Eric Dumazet <eric.dumazet@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 13 Oct 2011 07:56:41 +0000
Subject: igb: fix skb truesize underestimation
Patch-mainline: v3.2-rc1
Git-commit: 95b9c1dfb7b929f5f3b203ed95c28bdfd069d122
References: bnc#795297 FATE#313656

e1000 allocates half a page per skb fragment. We must account
PAGE_SIZE/2 increments on skb->truesize, not the actual frag length.

Signed-off-by: Eric Dumazet <eric.dumazet@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Acked-by: David Chang <dchang@suse.com>
Acked-by: Benjamin Poirier <bpoirier@suse.de>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/intel/igb/igb_main.c |    2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/igb/igb_main.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/igb/igb_main.c
@@ -5962,7 +5962,7 @@ static bool igb_clean_rx_irq(struct igb_
 
 			skb->len += length;
 			skb->data_len += length;
-			skb->truesize += length;
+			skb->truesize += PAGE_SIZE / 2;
 
 			if ((page_count(buffer_info->page) != 1) ||
 			    (page_to_nid(buffer_info->page) != current_node))
